snippet: The election commission ignored the demands of antigovernment demonstrators and said elections would go ahead on Feb. 2 despite efforts to sabotage them.
abstract: Thailand's Election Commission ignores demands of antigovernment demonstrators and says elections scheduled for February will go ahead despite continuing efforts to sabotage them.
lead_paragraph: The election commission ignored the demands of antigovernment demonstrators and said elections would go ahead on Feb. 2 despite efforts to sabotage them.

headline.main: Despite Protests in Thailand, Vote Will Go On, Panel Says
